61
00:05:39,070 --> 00:05:43,310
<i>From the moment they're born, 
people make countless choices.</i>

62
00:05:44,350 --> 00:05:49,050
<i>The worlds with the option you 
didn't choose are alternate realities.</i>

63
00:05:49,590 --> 00:05:52,350
<i>In other words, parallel worlds.</i>

64
00:05:52,350 --> 00:05:54,260
<i>And their existence has now 
been demonstrated.</i>

65
00:05:56,900 --> 00:06:00,830
<i>Moving into a parallel world 
is called Parallel Shifting.</i>

66
00:06:01,430 --> 00:06:05,490
<i>That said, it's not your physical 
body that does the moving.</i>

67
00:06:05,490 --> 00:06:08,440
<i>Your consciousness, termed 
your imaginality, trades places.</i>

68
00:06:09,750 --> 00:06:13,760
<i>Small Parallel Shifts are 
an everyday occurrence,</i>

69
00:06:13,760 --> 00:06:15,850
<i>but you basically never notice.</i>

70
00:06:17,090 --> 00:06:20,160
<i>When you can't find something
 where you left it,</i>

71
00:06:20,160 --> 00:06:23,230
<i>but then it's there when you double-check,</i>

72
00:06:23,230 --> 00:06:26,120
<i>it's often because 
of a small Parallel Shift.</i>

73
00:06:28,490 --> 00:06:30,730
<i>If we say your original world is "0",</i>

74
00:06:30,730 --> 00:06:35,410
<i>you Shifted from world 0, where you left
 the item there, to world 1, where you didn't,</i>

75
00:06:35,410 --> 00:06:37,270
